   183	## D4 — NOT NULL + migration strategy
   184	
   185	vec0 virtual tables do not support `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN`
   186	(sqlite-vec stores its columns in vec0-internal shadow tables;
   187	the surface is `CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE` or DROP+RECREATE). The
   188	migration is therefore necessarily a table rebuild, not an in-
   189	place ALTER.
   190	
   191	**Decision: land NOT NULL constraints from the start. The
   192	migration is a single transactional rebuild — CREATE new vec0
   193	under a staging name, INSERT...SELECT with `vec_quantize_binary`
   194	on the fly, DROP old, RENAME — and the writer enforces
   195	non-nullability from commit zero.**
   196	
   197	Migration shape (Pack 1, runs at `EngineRuntime::open` after the
   198	schema-version bump):
   199	
   200	```sql
   201	CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE vector_default_v2 USING vec0(
   202	  embedding float[<dim>],
   203	  embedding_bin bit[<dim>],
   204	  source_type TEXT partition key,
   205	  kind TEXT,
   206	  created_at INTEGER
   207	);
   208	
   209	INSERT INTO vector_default_v2(
   210	  rowid, embedding, embedding_bin, source_type, kind, created_at
   211	)
   212	SELECT
   213	  v.rowid,
   214	  v.embedding,
   215	  vec_quantize_binary(v.embedding),
   216	  -- source_type / kind / created_at come from _fathomdb_vector_rows
   217	  -- joined on write_cursor = vector_default.rowid (see lib.rs:2174-2175
   218	  -- comment: vec0 rowid IS the canonical row's write_cursor).
   219	  resolve_source_type_sql(vr.kind),     -- registered SQL function (see below)
   220	  vr.kind,
   221	  unixepoch()                            -- best-effort backfill; no original timestamp survives
   222	FROM vector_default v
   223	JOIN _fathomdb_vector_rows vr ON vr.write_cursor = v.rowid;
   224	
   225	DROP TABLE vector_default;
   226	ALTER TABLE vector_default_v2 RENAME TO vector_default;
   227	```
   228	
   229	The migration runs inside a single writer transaction. Per the
   230	ADR § 4 estimate it costs ~3 GB read + ~96 MB write on the 1 M-row
   231	fixture, ~64 s wall on the dev box — well under the existing
   232	workflow timeout and the existing AC-013 seed cost (562 s on
   233	canonical CI).
