Refs: [memo](</tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:105>), [HITL lock](</tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/plans/0.7.0-HITL-recommendations.md:135>), [fixture uses `doc`](</tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs:350>)
The memo explicitly expands the locked vocabulary from 6 values to 7 by admitting `"doc"`. The HITL record says Pack 1 “MUST use `source_type` as the vec0 partition_key,” and the locked vocabulary immediately above it is `email/article/paper/meeting/note/todo`; there is no approval here to add a synthetic 7th value.  
Because D3 changes a HITL-locked contract instead of implementing it, this is a blocking design violation. If `doc` must remain in tests, it needs a separate HITL/ADR update or the test fixture kind needs to be remapped without changing the locked vocabulary.

### 2. [high] The migration plan relies on vec0 rename support that the pinned sqlite-vec version does not establish
Refs: [memo migration](</tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/dev/design/0.7.0-vector-quant-pack1.md:183>), [engine migration path](</tmp/fdb-0.7.0-PVQ-P1-DESIGN-20260527T132416Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1207>), [SQLite virtual-table rule](https://www.sqlite.org/vtab.html), [sqlite-vec releases](https://github.com/asg017/sqlite-vec/releases)
The memo’s rebuild shape is `CREATE ... vector_default_v2` → copy rows → `DROP TABLE vector_default` → `ALTER TABLE vector_default_v2 RENAME TO vector_default`. SQLite allows neither `ADD COLUMN` on virtual tables nor arbitrary rename unless the module implements it; sqlite-vec’s release notes show `ALTER TABLE RENAME support` appearing in `v0.1.10-alpha.2` on April 1, 2026, while this repo is pinned to `=0.1.7`.  
That means the proposed Pack 1 migration is not validated for the version actually in use. The same section also invents an `operational_mutations` schema stamp, but the engine’s real migration framework is `migrate_with_event_sink(...)` plus `PRAGMA user_version`, so the gating story is mismatched as written.

